// Shared domain bootstrap for hook processes (mt#3019).
//
// A hook is its OWN entry point. The CLI's `cli.ts` and the MCP server both do
// two things at boot that a hook process does not inherit:
//
//   1. Load the tsyringe reflect polyfill. Domain classes reached through the
//      persistence factory are `@injectable()`; without `reflect-metadata` the
//      very IMPORT of `packages/domain/src/persistence/factory` throws
//      "tsyringe requires a reflect polyfill".
//   2. Initialize the process-global domain configuration system. Without it,
//      `PersistenceService.initialize()` throws "Configuration not initialized.
//      Call initializeConfiguration() first."
//
// Layer 1 is the one that bites first and is the easiest to miss: it throws at
// MODULE LOAD, OUTSIDE `resolvePersistenceProvider`'s try/catch, so it never
// becomes the documented `null` return — it propagates to whatever wraps the
// import. Layer 2 IS inside that try, so it degrades to `null` and reads as
// "DB unavailable". A hook missing layer 1 and a hook missing layer 2 therefore
// fail with completely different signatures, which is why mt#3019's original
// diagnosis named only layer 2.
//
// `record-subagent-invocation.ts` was missing BOTH for the entire life of the
// `subagent_invocations` table: 62 rows written between 2026-07-08 and
// 2026-07-22, zero of them carrying any hook-written column.
//
// @see mt#3019 — this module; the two-layer diagnosis and prod evidence
// @see mt#2958 — standalone-dup-probe.ts, where this pattern was first written inline
// @see mt#3046 — the entry-point smoke test that makes a dead bootstrap detectable
// @see packages/domain/src/config-setup.ts — the canonical setupConfiguration()

// Layer 1. STATIC and unconditional: it must be resolved before ANY domain
// module is imported, and importing THIS module is what guarantees that for a
// hook whose own domain imports are dynamic. Cheap — a polyfill install, no
// domain code loaded.
import "reflect-metadata";

